Commentary Text: Rahul Chahar to Chahar, out Stumped!! Smart keeping from QDK. Deepak Chahar doesn't trouble the scorers. He wanted to have a big piece of his younger brother and threw caution to the wind. In the process of slogging one, he dragged his back foot too far so much so that QDK barely had to appeal. Commentary Text: Boult to du Plessis, out Caught by de Kock!! This almost seemed like it was just a normal delivery and a normal appeal, wasn't for Faf though. He started walking the moment the ball went past his blade. Oh CSK, they are in deep, deep trouble. It's a teasing away swinger from Boult and Faf's feet are stuck in thick clay. They just don't move. Only the hands go searching and the finest of edges has been snaffled by the ever-exuberant QDK. de Kock went up in appeal straightaway and he did surprise some of his team-mates who assumed that the bat hit the ground, wasn't to be. du Plessis c de Kock b Boult 1(7)

Commentary Text: Bumrah to N Jagadeesan, out Caught by Suryakumar Yadav!! Jasprit Bumrah is on fire! Excellent seam position on this fullish length delivery as he lured Jagadeesan to have a poke outside off, the youngster finds it too hard to resist and he sends a thick, healthy edge straight into the bucket hands of SKY at wide first slip. With the ball moving, Jagadeesan should have left that alone, but he went for the booming drive which cost him his wicket. Right then, Bumrah on a hat-trick and guess who's facing?
